A toy OS for RISC-V.

This project is for me to learn RISC-V and operating systems. It is being developed on QEMU for now but will be, if possible, ported to MangoPi MQ-Pro - a cute pink SoC. I will try to make it as UNIX as I should, and POSIX-compatible hopefully.


References
==========

* RISC-V Spec Vol 1: Unprivileged ISA
* RISC-V Spec Vol 2: Privileged Architecture
* RISC-V Supervisor Binary Interface Specification
* The RISC-V Reader: An Open Architecture Atlas
* rCore-Tutorial-Book-v3 - rcore-os.cn
* The Design of the UNIX Operating System - Maurice J. Bach
* Modern Operating Systems - Andrew S. Tanenbaum, Herbert Bos


* linux-0.12
* rcore-os



